  "text": "What can investigators do with information they collect on selection biases in their studies? By knowing the extent of sampling bias and making estimates of the response rates of the populations not entered, one can model the results of a study performed with unbiased samples. For many studies, modeled study results will be substantially different from actual results only if selection biases are very large [CITATION_1] .",
